snippet: Egypt’s interim vice president said on Saturday that force could be used only as a last resort to disperse demonstrations held by supporters of Mohamed Morsi.
abstract: Egyptian interim Vice Pres Mohamed ElBaradei says force will be used only as last resort to disperse two sit-ins held by supporters of former Pres Mohamed Morsi.

byline.original: By KAREEM FAHIM and ASMAA AL ZOHAIRY

lead_paragraph: Egypt’s interim vice president said on Saturday that force could be used only as a last resort to disperse demonstrations held by supporters of Mohamed Morsi.

headline.main: Restraint Urged for Egypt’s Security Services
headline.print_headline: Restraint Urged for Egypt’s Security Services
